ull, "body": "<!--\r\nThank you for filing a bug report! \ud83d\udc1b Please provide a short summary of the bug,\r\nalong with any information you feel relevant to replicating the bug.\r\n-->\r\n\r\nI tried this code:\r\n\r\nhttps://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=bbc7ef716dadb46fb9a2d5db68519488\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: *explanation*\r\n\r\nThe code should compile.\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: *explanation*\r\n\r\nThe code doesn't compile, because the borrowck doesn't infer `'dangling` to actually be dangling.\r\n\r\nObviously, if the borrowck could infer `'dangling` to be dangling, the dropck should still prevent the `Drop` impl on `Holder`. But it doesn't even get to that point: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=069021ed82a0f32b5c4548ea46a6d2e5\r\n\r\nNote that this `Holder` and `Opaque` and etc stuff is constructed in such a way that it's impossible to observe `'dangling`, even if the compiler inferred it to be actually dangling.\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n<!--\r\nIf you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the\r\nbug also exists in the beta or nightly versions.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\n<version>\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nInclude a backtrace in the code block by setting `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` in your\r\nenvironment. E.g. `RUST_BACKTRACE=1 cargo build`.\r\n-->\r\n<details><summary>Backtrace</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n```\r\n<backtrace>\r\n```\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/97061/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/97061/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}